{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I have a doppelganger."},{"time":3000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":6000,"text":"Dr. Gero is a brilliant"},{"time":9000,"text":"but slightly mad scientist"},{"time":11000,"text":"in the \"Dragonball Z: Android Saga.\""},{"time":14000,"text":"If you look very carefully,"},{"time":16000,"text":"you see that his skull has been replaced"},{"time":19000,"text":"with a transparent Plexiglas dome"},{"time":21000,"text":"so that the workings of his brain can be observed"},{"time":24000,"text":"and also controlled with light."},{"time":27000,"text":"That's exactly what I do --"},{"time":29000,"text":"optical mind control."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":33000,"text":"But in contrast to my evil twin"},{"time":35000,"text":"who lusts after world domination,"},{"time":38000,"text":"my motives are not sinister."},{"time":41000,"text":"I control the brain"},{"time":43000,"text":"in order to understand how it works."},{"time":45000,"text":"Now wait a minute, you may say,"},{"time":47000,"text":"how can you go straight to controlling the brain"},{"time":50000,"text":"without understanding it first?"},{"time":52000,"text":"Isn't that putting the cart before the horse?"},{"time":56000,"text":"Many neuroscientists agree with this view"},{"time":59000,"text":"and think that understanding will come"},{"time":62000,"text":"from more detailed observation and analysis."},{"time":65000,"text":"They say, \"If we could record the activity of our neurons,"},{"time":69000,"text":"we would understand the brain.\""},{"time":72000,"text":"But think for a moment what that means."},{"time":75000,"text":"Even if we could measure"},{"time":77000,"text":"what every cell is doing at all times,"},{"time":79000,"text":"we would still have to make sense"},{"time":81000,"text":"of the recorded activity patterns,"},{"time":83000,"text":"and that's so difficult,"},{"time":85000,"text":"chances are we'll understand these patterns"},{"time":87000,"text":"just as little as the brains that produce them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90000,"text":"Take a look at what brain activity might look like."},{"time":93000,"text":"In this simulation, each black dot"},{"time":95000,"text":"is one nerve cell."},{"time":97000,"text":"The dot is visible"},{"time":99000,"text":"whenever a cell fires an electrical impulse."},{"time":101000,"text":"There's 10,000 neurons here."},{"time":103000,"text":"So you're looking at roughly one percent"},{"time":105000,"text":"of the brain of a cockroach."},{"time":109000,"text":"Your brains are about 100 million times"},{"time":112000,"text":"more complicated."},{"time":114000,"text":"Somewhere, in a pattern like this,"},{"time":116000,"text":"is you,"},{"time":118000,"text":"your perceptions,"},{"time":120000,"text":"your emotions, your memories,"},{"time":123000,"text":"your plans for the future."},{"time":125000,"text":"But we don't know where,"},{"time":127000,"text":"since we don't know how to read the pattern."},{"time":130000,"text":"We don't understand the code used by the brain."},{"time":133000,"text":"To make progress,"},{"time":135000,"text":"we need to break the code."},{"time":137000,"text":"But how?"},{"time":140000,"text":"An experienced code-breaker will tell you"},{"time":142000,"text":"that in order to figure out what the symbols in a code mean,"},{"time":145000,"text":"it's essential to be able to play with them,"},{"time":148000,"text":"to rearrange them at will."},{"time":150000,"text":"So in this situation too,"},{"time":152000,"text":"to decode the information"},{"time":154000,"text":"contained in patterns like this,"},{"time":156000,"text":"watching alone won't do."},{"time":158000,"text":"We need to rearrange the pattern."},{"time":160000,"text":"In other words,"},{"time":162000,"text":"instead of recording the activity of neurons,"},{"time":164000,"text":"we need to control it."},{"time":166000,"text":"It's not essential that we can control"},{"time":168000,"text":"the activity of all neurons in the brain, just some."},{"time":171000,"text":"The more targeted our interventions, the better."},{"time":173000,"text":"And I'll show you in a moment"},{"time":175000,"text":"how we can achieve the necessary precision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178000,"text":"And since I'm realistic, rather than grandiose,"},{"time":181000,"text":"I don't claim that the ability to control the function of the nervous system"},{"time":184000,"text":"will at once unravel all its mysteries."},{"time":187000,"text":"But we'll certainly learn a lot."},{"time":192000,"text":"Now, I'm by no means"},{"time":194000,"text":"the first person to realize"},{"time":196000,"text":"how powerful a tool intervention is."},{"time":199000,"text":"The history of attempts"},{"time":201000,"text":"to tinker with the function of the nervous system"},{"time":203000,"text":"is long and illustrious."},{"time":205000,"text":"It dates back at least 200 years,"},{"time":208000,"text":"to Galvani's famous experiments"},{"time":210000,"text":"in the late 18th century and beyond."},{"time":214000,"text":"Galvani showed that a frog's legs twitched"},{"time":217000,"text":"when he connected the lumbar nerve"},{"time":219000,"text":"to a source of electrical current."},{"time":222000,"text":"This experiment revealed the first, and perhaps most fundamental,"},{"time":225000,"text":"nugget of the neural code:"},{"time":227000,"text":"that information is written in the form"},{"time":229000,"text":"of electrical impulses."},{"time":233000,"text":"Galvani's approach"},{"time":235000,"text":"of probing the nervous system with electrodes"},{"time":237000,"text":"has remained state-of-the-art until today,"},{"time":240000,"text":"despite a number of drawbacks."},{"time":243000,"text":"Sticking wires into the brain is obviously rather crude."},{"time":246000,"text":"It's hard to do in animals that run around,"},{"time":248000,"text":"and there is a physical limit"},{"time":250000,"text":"to the number of wires"},{"time":252000,"text":"that can be inserted simultaneously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255000,"text":"So around the turn of the last century,"},{"time":257000,"text":"I started to think,"},{"time":259000,"text":"\"Wouldn't it be wonderful if one could take this logic"},{"time":262000,"text":"and turn it upside down?\""},{"time":264000,"text":"So instead of inserting a wire"},{"time":266000,"text":"into one spot of the brain,"},{"time":269000,"text":"re-engineer the brain itself"},{"time":271000,"text":"so that some of its neural elements"},{"time":274000,"text":"become responsive to diffusely broadcast signals"},{"time":277000,"text":"such as a flash of light."},{"time":280000,"text":"Such an approach would literally, in a flash of light,"},{"time":283000,"text":"overcome many of the obstacles to discovery."},{"time":286000,"text":"First, it's clearly a non-invasive,"},{"time":289000,"text":"wireless form of communication."},{"time":292000,"text":"And second, just as in a radio broadcast,"},{"time":294000,"text":"you can communicate with many receivers at once."},{"time":297000,"text":"You don't need to know where these receivers are,"},{"time":300000,"text":"and it doesn't matter if these receivers move --"},{"time":302000,"text":"just think of the stereo in your car."},{"time":305000,"text":"It gets even better,"},{"time":308000,"text":"for it turns out that we can fabricate the receivers"},{"time":311000,"text":"out of materials that are encoded in DNA."},{"time":314000,"text":"So each nerve cell"},{"time":316000,"text":"with the right genetic makeup"},{"time":318000,"text":"will spontaneously produce a receiver"},{"time":321000,"text":"that allows us to control its function."},{"time":324000,"text":"I hope you'll appreciate"},{"time":326000,"text":"the beautiful simplicity"},{"time":328000,"text":"of this concept."},{"time":330000,"text":"There's no high-tech gizmos here,"},{"time":332000,"text":"just biology revealed through biology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336000,"text":"Now let's take a look at these miraculous receivers up close."},{"time":339000,"text":"As we zoom in on one of these purple neurons,"},{"time":342000,"text":"we see that its outer membrane"},{"time":344000,"text":"is studded with microscopic pores."},{"time":346000,"text":"Pores like these conduct electrical current"},{"time":348000,"text":"and are responsible"},{"time":350000,"text":"for all the communication in the nervous system."},{"time":352000,"text":"But these pores here are special."},{"time":354000,"text":"They are coupled to light receptors"},{"time":356000,"text":"similar to the ones in your eyes."},{"time":359000,"text":"Whenever a flash of light hits the receptor,"},{"time":361000,"text":"the pore opens, an electrical current is switched on,"},{"time":364000,"text":"and the neuron fires electrical impulses."},{"time":367000,"text":"Because the light-activated pore is encoded in DNA,"},{"time":370000,"text":"we can achieve incredible precision."},{"time":373000,"text":"This is because,"},{"time":375000,"text":"although each cell in our bodies"},{"time":377000,"text":"contains the same set of genes,"},{"time":379000,"text":"different mixes of genes get turned on and off"},{"time":381000,"text":"in different cells."},{"time":383000,"text":"You can exploit this to make sure"},{"time":385000,"text":"that only some neurons"},{"time":387000,"text":"contain our light-activated pore and others don't."},{"time":390000,"text":"So in this cartoon, the bluish white cell"},{"time":392000,"text":"in the upper-left corner"},{"time":394000,"text":"does not respond to light"},{"time":396000,"text":"because it lacks the light-activated pore."},{"time":399000,"text":"The approach works so well"},{"time":401000,"text":"that we can write purely artificial messages"},{"time":403000,"text":"directly to the brain."},{"time":405000,"text":"In this example, each electrical impulse,"},{"time":407000,"text":"each deflection on the trace,"},{"time":410000,"text":"is caused by a brief pulse of light."},{"time":413000,"text":"And the approach, of course, also works"},{"time":415000,"text":"in moving, behaving animals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418000,"text":"This is the first ever such experiment,"},{"time":420000,"text":"sort of the optical equivalent of Galvani's."},{"time":423000,"text":"It was done six or seven years ago"},{"time":425000,"text":"by my then graduate student, Susana Lima."},{"time":428000,"text":"Susana had engineered the fruit fly on the left"},{"time":431000,"text":"so that just two out of the 200,000 cells in its brain"},{"time":435000,"text":"expressed the light-activated pore."},{"time":438000,"text":"You're familiar with these cells"},{"time":440000,"text":"because they are the ones that frustrate you"},{"time":442000,"text":"when you try to swat the fly."},{"time":444000,"text":"They trained the escape reflex that makes the fly jump into the air"},{"time":447000,"text":"and fly away whenever you move your hand in position."},{"time":451000,"text":"And you can see here that the flash of light has exactly the same effect."},{"time":454000,"text":"The animal jumps, it spreads its wings, it vibrates them,"},{"time":457000,"text":"but it can't actually take off"},{"time":459000,"text":"because the fly is sandwiched between two glass plates."},{"time":463000,"text":"Now to make sure that this was no reaction of the fly"},{"time":465000,"text":"to a flash it could see,"},{"time":468000,"text":"Susana did a simple"},{"time":470000,"text":"but brutally effective experiment."},{"time":472000,"text":"She cut the heads off of her flies."},{"time":476000,"text":"These headless bodies can live for about a day,"},{"time":479000,"text":"but they don't do much."},{"time":481000,"text":"They just stand around"},{"time":484000,"text":"and groom excessively."},{"time":487000,"text":"So it seems that the only trait that survives decapitation is vanity."},{"time":490000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":495000,"text":"Anyway, as you'll see in a moment,"},{"time":497000,"text":"Susana was able to turn on the flight motor"},{"time":500000,"text":"of what's the equivalent of the spinal cord of these flies"},{"time":503000,"text":"and get some of the headless bodies"},{"time":505000,"text":"to actually take off and fly away."},{"time":512000,"text":"They didn't get very far, obviously."},{"time":515000,"text":"Since we took these first steps,"},{"time":517000,"text":"the field of optogenetics has exploded."},{"time":520000,"text":"And there are now hundreds of labs"},{"time":522000,"text":"using these approaches."}]},{"cues":[{"time":524000,"text":"And we've come a long way"},{"time":526000,"text":"since Galvani's and Susana's first successes"},{"time":529000,"text":"in making animals twitch or jump."},{"time":531000,"text":"We can now actually interfere with their psychology"},{"time":534000,"text":"in rather profound ways,"},{"time":536000,"text":"as I'll show you in my last example,"},{"time":538000,"text":"which is directed at a familiar question."},{"time":541000,"text":"Life is a string of choices"},{"time":544000,"text":"creating a constant pressure to decide what to do next."},{"time":548000,"text":"We cope with this pressure by having brains,"},{"time":551000,"text":"and within our brains, decision-making centers"},{"time":554000,"text":"that I've called here the \"Actor.\""},{"time":558000,"text":"The Actor implements a policy that takes into account"},{"time":561000,"text":"the state of the environment"},{"time":563000,"text":"and the context in which we operate."},{"time":566000,"text":"Our actions change the environment, or context,"},{"time":569000,"text":"and these changes are then fed back into the decision loop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573000,"text":"Now to put some neurobiological meat"},{"time":576000,"text":"on this abstract model,"},{"time":578000,"text":"we constructed a simple one-dimensional world"},{"time":580000,"text":"for our favorite subject, fruit flies."},{"time":583000,"text":"Each chamber in these two vertical stacks"},{"time":585000,"text":"contains one fly."},{"time":587000,"text":"The left and the right halves of the chamber"},{"time":590000,"text":"are filled with two different odors,"},{"time":592000,"text":"and a security camera watches"},{"time":594000,"text":"as the flies pace up and down between them."},{"time":597000,"text":"Here's some such CCTV footage."},{"time":599000,"text":"Whenever a fly reaches the midpoint of the chamber"},{"time":602000,"text":"where the two odor streams meet,"},{"time":604000,"text":"it has to make a decision."},{"time":606000,"text":"It has to decide whether to turn around"},{"time":608000,"text":"and stay in the same odor,"},{"time":610000,"text":"or whether to cross the midline"},{"time":612000,"text":"and try something new."},{"time":614000,"text":"These decisions are clearly a reflection"},{"time":617000,"text":"of the Actor's policy."},{"time":621000,"text":"Now for an intelligent being like our fly,"},{"time":624000,"text":"this policy is not written in stone"},{"time":627000,"text":"but rather changes as the animal learns from experience."},{"time":630000,"text":"We can incorporate such an element"},{"time":632000,"text":"of adaptive intelligence into our model"},{"time":635000,"text":"by assuming that the fly's brain"},{"time":637000,"text":"contains not only an Actor,"},{"time":639000,"text":"but a different group of cells,"},{"time":641000,"text":"a \"Critic,\" that provides a running commentary"},{"time":644000,"text":"on the Actor's choices."},{"time":646000,"text":"You can think of this nagging inner voice"},{"time":649000,"text":"as sort of the brain's equivalent"},{"time":651000,"text":"of the Catholic Church,"},{"time":653000,"text":"if you're an Austrian like me,"},{"time":656000,"text":"or the super-ego, if you're Freudian,"},{"time":659000,"text":"or your mother, if you're Jewish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":665000,"text":"Now obviously,"},{"time":667000,"text":"the Critic is a key ingredient"},{"time":670000,"text":"in what makes us intelligent."},{"time":672000,"text":"So we set out to identify"},{"time":674000,"text":"the cells in the fly's brain"},{"time":676000,"text":"that played the role of the Critic."},{"time":678000,"text":"And the logic of our experiment was simple."},{"time":681000,"text":"We thought if we could use our optical remote control"},{"time":684000,"text":"to activate the cells of the Critic,"},{"time":687000,"text":"we should be able, artificially, to nag the Actor"},{"time":690000,"text":"into changing its policy."},{"time":692000,"text":"In other words,"},{"time":694000,"text":"the fly should learn from mistakes"},{"time":696000,"text":"that it thought it had made"},{"time":698000,"text":"but, in reality, it had not made."},{"time":701000,"text":"So we bred flies"},{"time":703000,"text":"whose brains were more or less randomly peppered"},{"time":706000,"text":"with cells that were light addressable."},{"time":708000,"text":"And then we took these flies"},{"time":710000,"text":"and allowed them to make choices."},{"time":712000,"text":"And whenever they made one of the two choices,"},{"time":714000,"text":"chose one odor,"},{"time":716000,"text":"in this case the blue one over the orange one,"},{"time":718000,"text":"we switched on the lights."},{"time":720000,"text":"If the Critic was among the optically activated cells,"},{"time":723000,"text":"the result of this intervention"},{"time":725000,"text":"should be a change in policy."},{"time":728000,"text":"The fly should learn to avoid"},{"time":730000,"text":"the optically reinforced odor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732000,"text":"Here's what happened in two instances:"},{"time":735000,"text":"We're comparing two strains of flies,"},{"time":738000,"text":"each of them having"},{"time":740000,"text":"about 100 light-addressable cells in their brains,"},{"time":742000,"text":"shown here in green on the left and on the right."},{"time":745000,"text":"What's common among these groups of cells"},{"time":748000,"text":"is that they all produce the neurotransmitter dopamine."},{"time":751000,"text":"But the identities of the individual"},{"time":753000,"text":"dopamine-producing neurons"},{"time":755000,"text":"are clearly largely different on the left and on the right."},{"time":758000,"text":"Optically activating"},{"time":760000,"text":"these hundred or so cells"},{"time":762000,"text":"into two strains of flies"},{"time":764000,"text":"has dramatically different consequences."},{"time":766000,"text":"If you look first at the behavior"},{"time":768000,"text":"of the fly on the right,"},{"time":770000,"text":"you can see that whenever it reaches the midpoint of the chamber"},{"time":773000,"text":"where the two odors meet,"},{"time":775000,"text":"it marches straight through, as it did before."},{"time":778000,"text":"Its behavior is completely unchanged."},{"time":780000,"text":"But the behavior of the fly on the left is very different."},{"time":783000,"text":"Whenever it comes up to the midpoint,"},{"time":786000,"text":"it pauses,"},{"time":788000,"text":"it carefully scans the odor interface"},{"time":790000,"text":"as if it was sniffing out its environment,"},{"time":792000,"text":"and then it turns around."},{"time":794000,"text":"This means that the policy that the Actor implements"},{"time":797000,"text":"now includes an instruction to avoid the odor"},{"time":799000,"text":"that's in the right half of the chamber."},{"time":802000,"text":"This means that the Critic"},{"time":804000,"text":"must have spoken in that animal,"},{"time":806000,"text":"and that the Critic must be contained"},{"time":808000,"text":"among the dopamine-producing neurons on the left,"},{"time":811000,"text":"but not among the dopamine producing neurons on the right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":814000,"text":"Through many such experiments,"},{"time":817000,"text":"we were able to narrow down"},{"time":819000,"text":"the identity of the Critic"},{"time":821000,"text":"to just 12 cells."},{"time":823000,"text":"These 12 cells, as shown here in green,"},{"time":826000,"text":"send the output to a brain structure"},{"time":828000,"text":"called the \"mushroom body,\""},{"time":830000,"text":"which is shown here in gray."},{"time":832000,"text":"We know from our formal model"},{"time":834000,"text":"that the brain structure"},{"time":836000,"text":"at the receiving end of the Critic's commentary is the Actor."},{"time":839000,"text":"So this anatomy suggests"},{"time":841000,"text":"that the mushroom bodies have something to do"},{"time":844000,"text":"with action choice."},{"time":846000,"text":"Based on everything we know about the mushroom bodies,"},{"time":848000,"text":"this makes perfect sense."},{"time":850000,"text":"In fact, it makes so much sense"},{"time":852000,"text":"that we can construct an electronic toy circuit"},{"time":855000,"text":"that simulates the behavior of the fly."},{"time":858000,"text":"In this electronic toy circuit,"},{"time":861000,"text":"the mushroom body neurons are symbolized"},{"time":863000,"text":"by the vertical bank of blue LEDs"},{"time":866000,"text":"in the center of the board."},{"time":869000,"text":"These LED's are wired to sensors"},{"time":871000,"text":"that detect the presence of odorous molecules in the air."},{"time":875000,"text":"Each odor activates a different combination of sensors,"},{"time":878000,"text":"which in turn activates"},{"time":880000,"text":"a different odor detector in the mushroom body."},{"time":883000,"text":"So the pilot in the cockpit of the fly,"},{"time":885000,"text":"the Actor,"},{"time":887000,"text":"can tell which odor is present"},{"time":889000,"text":"simply by looking at which of the blue LEDs lights up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894000,"text":"What the Actor does with this information"},{"time":896000,"text":"depends on its policy,"},{"time":898000,"text":"which is stored in the strengths of the connection,"},{"time":900000,"text":"between the odor detectors"},{"time":902000,"text":"and the motors"},{"time":904000,"text":"that power the fly's evasive actions."},{"time":907000,"text":"If the connection is weak, the motors will stay off"},{"time":909000,"text":"and the fly will continue straight on its course."},{"time":912000,"text":"If the connection is strong, the motors will turn on"},{"time":915000,"text":"and the fly will initiate a turn."},{"time":918000,"text":"Now consider a situation"},{"time":920000,"text":"in which the motors stay off,"},{"time":922000,"text":"the fly continues on its path"},{"time":925000,"text":"and it suffers some painful consequence"},{"time":927000,"text":"such as getting zapped."},{"time":929000,"text":"In a situation like this,"},{"time":931000,"text":"we would expect the Critic to speak up"},{"time":933000,"text":"and to tell the Actor"},{"time":935000,"text":"to change its policy."},{"time":937000,"text":"We have created such a situation, artificially,"},{"time":940000,"text":"by turning on the critic with a flash of light."},{"time":943000,"text":"That caused a strengthening of the connections"},{"time":946000,"text":"between the currently active odor detector"},{"time":949000,"text":"and the motors."},{"time":951000,"text":"So the next time"},{"time":953000,"text":"the fly finds itself facing the same odor again,"},{"time":956000,"text":"the connection is strong enough to turn on the motors"},{"time":959000,"text":"and to trigger an evasive maneuver."}]},{"cues":[{"time":964000,"text":"I don't know about you,"},{"time":967000,"text":"but I find it exhilarating to see"},{"time":970000,"text":"how vague psychological notions"},{"time":973000,"text":"evaporate and give rise"},{"time":975000,"text":"to a physical, mechanistic understanding of the mind,"},{"time":978000,"text":"even if it's the mind of the fly."},{"time":981000,"text":"This is one piece of good news."},{"time":984000,"text":"The other piece of good news,"},{"time":986000,"text":"for a scientist at least,"},{"time":988000,"text":"is that much remains to be discovered."},{"time":991000,"text":"In the experiments I told you about,"},{"time":993000,"text":"we have lifted the identity of the Critic,"},{"time":996000,"text":"but we still have no idea"},{"time":998000,"text":"how the Critic does its job."},{"time":1000000,"text":"Come to think of it, knowing when you're wrong"},{"time":1002000,"text":"without a teacher, or your mother, telling you,"},{"time":1005000,"text":"is a very hard problem."},{"time":1007000,"text":"There are some ideas in computer science"},{"time":1009000,"text":"and in artificial intelligence"},{"time":1011000,"text":"as to how this might be done,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"but we still haven't solved"},{"time":1015000,"text":"a single example"},{"time":1017000,"text":"of how intelligent behavior"},{"time":1020000,"text":"springs from the physical interactions"},{"time":1022000,"text":"in living matter."},{"time":1024000,"text":"I think we'll get there in the not too distant future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1027000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}